{"title_page": "Guess What (song)", "text_new": "{{short description|2002 single by Syleena Johnson}}\n{{under construction}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Guess What\n| cover      = Syleena-johnson-guess-what.jpg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Syleena Johnson]]\n| album      = [[Chapter 2: The Voice]]\n| released   = August 20, 2002\n| format     = {{flat list |\n*[[Compact Disc single|CD single]]\n*[[12-inch single]]}}\n| recorded   = 2001; Rock Land Studios<br><small>([[Chicago, Illinois]])</small> <br> Battery Studios<br><small>([[New York City]], [[New York (state)|New York]])</small>\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = {{hlist|[[Contemporary R&B|R&B]]|[[soul music|soul]]}}\n| length     = 3:32\n| label      = [[Jive Records]]\n| writer     = [[R. Kelly|Robert Kelly]]\n| producer   = R. Kelly\n| prev_title = Tonight I'm Gonna Let Go\n| prev_year  = 2002\n| next_title = [[Faithful to You]]\n| next_year  = 2003\n}}\n\"'''Guess What'''\" is a song by American recording artist [[Syleena Johnson]] from her second studio album, ''[[Chapter 2: The Voice]]''. Written and produced by [[R. Kelly]], the song was released as the album's second [[single (music)|single]] on August 20, 2002. It became Johnson's first number-one single as a lead artist in the US, peaking at number 1 atop the [[Adult R&B Songs]] chart and staying there for 46 weeks. Elsewhere released in April 2006, \"Guess What\" also saw success in the [[UK R&B Singles and Albums Charts|UK]] and New Zealand, reaching the top forty in both countries.\n\nAn accompanying music video was directed by [[Fab Five Freddy]]. The video depicts Johnson's conflict with her unfaithful lover. A [[remix]] entitled \"Guess What (Guess Again)\" was released as a single and featured [[R. Kelly]]'s vocals as well as production and writing.\n\n== Composition and critical reception ==\n\"Guess What\" was written and produced by [[R. Kelly]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Henderson |first=Alex |url= https://www.allmusic.com/album/chapter-2-the-voice-mw0000225024 |title=Chapter 2: The Voice \u2013 Syleena Johnson \u2013 Review |publisher=[[Allmusic]]. [[Rovi Corporation]] |accessdate=July 4, 2011}}</ref>\n\n==Chart performance==\n\"Guess What\" was first released in the United States, where a promo-only [[12 inch]] single was issued to radio airplay in May 2002. Officially released to radio and retailers by August 2002,<ref name=\"amazonus\">{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/Guess-What-Syleena-Johnson/dp/B0014NTMZQ|title=Guess What - Single|accessdate=2015-12-29}}</ref> the song debuted on the US [[Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Airplay]] chart.<ref name=\"billlboardbiz1\">{{cite web|title=R&B/Hip-Hop Airplay Chart|url=https://assets.billboard.com/charts/hot-r-and-b-hip-hop-airplay/2003-03-22|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]]}}</ref> It spent 28 weeks on the chart, peaking at number twenty-nine.<ref name=\"billlboardbiz1\"/> It initially entered the [[Bubbling Under Hot 100]] at number nineteen on the chart, where it moved up to number four a few weeks later.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.billboard.com/charts/bubbling-under-hot-100-singles/2003-04-12|title=Music: Billboard Bubbling Under Hot 100 Chart|publisher=}}</ref> It later moved to the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]], peaking at number eighty-nine. As of 2018, the single remains Johnson's only entry on the chart.<ref name=\"billlboardbiz1\"/> \"Guess What\" fared better on many of the ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' [[Billboard charts|component charts]], including number twenty-nine on the [[Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs]] chart, and number one for eight consecutive weeks on the [[Adult R&B Songs]] chart.<ref name=\"allmusicawards\">{{cite web|title=Awards > Billboard Singles|url=https://www.allmusic.com/artist/syleena-johnson-mn0000757093/awards|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|publisher=[[Allmusic]]|accessdate=2016-06-27}}</ref> \"Guess What\" also reached number sixteen on the [[Canadian Singles Chart]].<ref name=\"allmusicawards\"/>\n\nOutside of the United States, \"Guess What\" peaked within the top twenty of the charts in New Zealand and the United Kingdom. In the United Kingdom, \"Guess What\" entered the [[UK R&B Singles Chart]] at number 18. It entered the top 20 at number nineteen on the [[New Zealand Singles Chart]]. It also entered the top forty on the [[European Hot 100 Singles]] and the [[Dutch Top 40]].\n\n==Charts==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" \n|-\n!scope=\"col\"| Chart (2002)\n!scope=\"col\"| Peak<br />position\n|-\n{{singlechart|Australia|22|artist=Syleena Johnson|song=Guess What}}\n|-\n|Europe ([[European Hot 100 Singles|Eurochart Hot 100]])<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.americanradiohistory.com/UK/Music-and-Media/00s/2002/MM-2002-10-05.pdf|title=Eurochart Hot 100 Singles|magazine=[[Music & Media]]|volume=20|issue=41|page=9|date=October 5, 2002|access-date=February 10, 2020}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|38\n|-\n|France ([[Syndicat National de l'\u00c9dition Phonographique|SNEP]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://lescharts.com/weekchart.asp?cat=s&year=2002&date=20021012|title=lescharts.com - Les charts fran\u00e7ais|date=October 12, 2002|website=lescharts.com|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|92\n|-\n|Germany ([[GfK Entertainment charts|Official German Charts]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.offiziellecharts.de/charts/single/for-date-1033099200000|title=Offizielle Deutsche Charts - Offizielle Deutsche Charts|last=|first=|date=September 27, 2002|website=www.offiziellecharts.de|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|64\n|-\n|Netherlands ([[Dutch Top 40]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://top40-charts.com/chart.php?cid=13&date=2002-11-02|title=Netherlands Top 20 @ Top40-Charts.com|date=November 2, 2002|website=top40-charts.com|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|35\n|-\n{{singlechart|Dutch100|67|artist=Syleena Johnson|song=Guess What}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|New Zealand|19|artist=Syleena Johnson|song=Guess What}}\n|-\n| [[UK R&B Singles and Albums Charts|UK R&B]] (Official Charts Company)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/charts/r-and-b-singles-chart/20021027/114/|title=Official R&B Singles Chart Top 40 27 October 2002 - 02 November 2002|work=[[Official Charts Company]]}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|18\n|-\n|-\n|Canada ([[Canadian Singles Chart|Nielsen SoundScan]])<ref name=\"allmusic\">{{cite web |url={{Allmusic|class=album|id=r467306|pure_url=yes}} |title=Chapter 2: The Voice > Charts & Awards > Billboard Singles |work=[[Allmusic]] |accessdate=June 17, 2009}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|16\n|-\n{{singlechart|Billboardadultrandbsongs|1|artist=Syleena Johnson|song=Guess What|accessdate=June 20, 2014}}\n|-\n| US [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=OQ0EAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA78&dq=syleena+johnson+2002+billboard+hot+100&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwj0wZLmpMToAhWHZd8KHR1OCFwQ6AEIMjAC#v=onepage&q=syleena%20johnson%202002%20billboard%20hot%20100|title=Billboard - Nov 9, 2002 - Page 78|website=[[Google Books]]|date=November 9, 2002}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|89\n|-\n{{singlechart|Billboardrandbhiphop|29|artist=Syleena Johnson|song=Guess What|accessdate=June 20, 2014}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Billboardrandbhiphopairplay|22|artist=Syleena Johnson|song=Guess What|accessdate=June 20, 2014}}\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Syleena Johnson}}\n\n[[Category:2002 singles]]\n[[Category:2002 songs]]\n[[Category:Syleena Johnson songs]]\n[[Category:Songs written by R. Kelly]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2002 single by Syleena Johnson}}\n{{under construction}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Guess What\n| cover      = Syleena-johnson-guess-what.jpg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Syleena Johnson]]\n| album      = [[Chapter 2: The Voice]]\n| released   = August 20, 2002\n| format     = {{flat list |\n*[[Compact Disc single|CD single]]\n*[[12-inch single]]}}\n| recorded   = 2001; Rock Land Studios<br><small>([[Chicago, Illinois]])</small> <br> Battery Studios<br><small>([[New York City]], [[New York (state)|New York]])</small>\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = {{hlist|[[Contemporary R&B|R&B]]|[[soul music|soul]]}}\n| length     = 3:32\n| label      = [[Jive Records]]\n| writer     = [[R. Kelly|Robert Kelly]]\n| producer   = R. Kelly\n| prev_title = Tonight I'm Gonna Let Go\n| prev_year  = 2002\n| next_title = [[Faithful to You]]\n| next_year  = 2003\n}}\n\"'''Guess What'''\" is a song by American recording artist [[Syleena Johnson]] from her second studio album, ''[[Chapter 2: The Voice]]''. Written and produced by [[R. Kelly]], the song was released as the album's second [[single (music)|single]] on August 20, 2002. It became Johnson's first number-one single as a lead artist in the US, peaking at number 1 atop the [[Adult R&B Songs]] chart and staying there for 46 weeks. Elsewhere released in April 2006, \"Guess What\" also saw success in the [[UK R&B Singles and Albums Charts|UK]] and New Zealand, reaching the top forty in both countries.\n\nAn accompanying music video was directed by [[Fab Five Freddy]]. A [[remix]] entitled \"Guess What (Guess Again)\" was released as a single and featured [[R. Kelly]]'s vocals as well as production and writing.\n\n== Composition and critical reception ==\n\"Guess What\" was written and produced by [[R. Kelly]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Henderson |first=Alex |url= https://www.allmusic.com/album/chapter-2-the-voice-mw0000225024 |title=Chapter 2: The Voice \u2013 Syleena Johnson \u2013 Review |publisher=[[Allmusic]]. [[Rovi Corporation]] |accessdate=July 4, 2011}}</ref>\n\n==Chart performance==\n\"Guess What\" was first released in the United States, where a promo-only [[12 inch]] single was issued to radio airplay in May 2002. Officially released to radio and retailers by August 2002,<ref name=\"amazonus\">{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/Guess-What-Syleena-Johnson/dp/B0014NTMZQ|title=Guess What - Single|accessdate=2015-12-29}}</ref> the song debuted on the US [[Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Airplay]] chart.<ref name=\"billlboardbiz1\">{{cite web|title=R&B/Hip-Hop Airplay Chart|url=https://assets.billboard.com/charts/hot-r-and-b-hip-hop-airplay/2003-03-22|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]]}}</ref> It spent 28 weeks on the chart, peaking at number twenty-nine.<ref name=\"billlboardbiz1\"/> It initially entered the [[Bubbling Under Hot 100]] at number nineteen on the chart, where it moved up to number four a few weeks later.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.billboard.com/charts/bubbling-under-hot-100-singles/2003-04-12|title=Music: Billboard Bubbling Under Hot 100 Chart|publisher=}}</ref> It later moved to the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]], peaking at number eighty-nine. As of 2018, the single remains Johnson's only entry on the chart.<ref name=\"billlboardbiz1\"/> \"Guess What\" fared better on many of the ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' [[Billboard charts|component charts]], including number twenty-nine on the [[Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs]] chart, and number one for eight consecutive weeks on the [[Adult R&B Songs]] chart.<ref name=\"allmusicawards\">{{cite web|title=Awards > Billboard Singles|url=https://www.allmusic.com/artist/syleena-johnson-mn0000757093/awards|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|publisher=[[Allmusic]]|accessdate=2016-06-27}}</ref> \"Guess What\" also reached number sixteen on the [[Canadian Singles Chart]].<ref name=\"allmusicawards\"/>\n\nOutside of the United States, \"Guess What\" peaked within the top twenty of the charts in New Zealand and the United Kingdom. In the United Kingdom, \"Guess What\" entered the [[UK R&B Singles Chart]] at number 18. It entered the top 20 at number nineteen on the [[New Zealand Singles Chart]]. It also entered the top forty on the [[European Hot 100 Singles]] and the [[Dutch Top 40]].\n\n==Charts==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable p