{"title_page": "Ant\u00f4nio Martoni", "text_new": "{{Orphan|date=April 2020}}\n\n{{infobox Rugby biography\n| image = \n|image_size=\n| caption =\n| birthname=\n| birth_date = 1961\n| birth_place = [[S\u00e3o Paulo]]\n| height =\n| weight =\n| ru_position =Hooker, Scrumhalf\n| ru_amateuryears = \n| ru_amateurclubs =Col\u00e9gio S\u00e3o Luiz<br>Objetivo<br>Mau\u00e1<br>Nippon<br>Joerg Bruder<br>Bandeirantes\n| ru_clubyears = \n| ru_proclubs =\n| ru_clubcaps = \n| ru_clubpoints = \n| ru_nationalyears =1979-1995\n| ru_nationalteam = {{ru|Brazil}}\n| ru_nationalcaps =70\n| ru_nationalpoints =\n| ru_sevensnationalyears = \n| ru_sevensnationalteam  =\n| ru_sevensnationalcomp  = \n| ru_coachyears = \n| ru_coachclubs ={{ru|Brazil}}\n}}\n'''Ant\u00f4nio Martoni Neto''' (born [[S\u00e3o Paulo]], 1961) is a Brazilian former rugby union player, coach and he is currently a rugby commentator for [[ESPN]] Brazil. He played first as a hooker, later moving to scrum-half. He is professionally a lawyer. He is usually considered one of the best Brazilian rugby union players of ever.\n\nMartoni started his player career at Col\u00e9gio S\u00e3o Luiz. He later would play for Objetivo, Mau\u00e1, Nippon, Joerg Bruder and Bandeirantes, a team he helped to start, in 1983, and he would represent most of his career, finished in 2000. He also played football as a youngster and decided for rugby union over football at 18. He won for Bandeirantes the Brazilian Championship B Series title, in 1983, and 2 Brazilian Championship titles, in 1988 and 1995. He also won 4 S\u00e3o Paulo State Championship titles, in 1990, 1996, 1998 and 2000.\n\nMartoni had more than 70 caps for [[Brazil national rugby union team|Brazil]], from 1979 to 1995. He had his debut at the [[South American Rugby Championship]], at 7 October 1979, in a 53-6 loss to [[Chile national rugby union team|Chile]], in [[Vi\u00f1a del Mar]]. He scored his first points in that game.\n\nHe became a coach when he finished his player career, in 2000. He was the coach of Bandeirantes and at the same time of Brazil national team. He achieved Brazil first international titles, at the [[South American Rugby Championship]] B, in 2000 and 2002. He was also in charge of the Brazilian side during the [[2003 Rugby World Cup]] qualifyings, and after two years without losses, he managed to improve his [[International Rugby Board|IRB]] ranking position from 69th to 36th.<ref>[http://www.portaldorugby.com.br/noticia/39-entrevistas/1693-noticia-1793 Falando de Rugby: Ant\u00f4nio Martoni, Interview, 10 February 2011, Portal do Rugby (Portuguese)]{{dead link|date=October 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n\nMartoni is a rugby commentator for ESPN since 2003, he has been covering the most important international competitions for the sports channel.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.portaldorugby.com.br/noticia/39-entrevistas/1693-noticia-1793 Falando de Rugby: Ant\u00f4nio Martoni, Interview, 10 February 2011, Portal do Rugby (Portuguese)]{{dead link|date=October 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Martoni, Antonio}}\n[[Category:1961 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Brazilian rugby union players]]\n[[Category:Brazilian rugby union coaches]]\n[[Category:Rugby union hookers]]\n[[Category:Rugby union fly-halves]]\n\n\n{{Brazil-rugbyunion-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{infobox Rugby biography\n| image = \n|image_size=\n| caption =\n| birthname=\n| birth_date = 1961\n| birth_place = [[S\u00e3o Paulo]]\n| height =\n| weight =\n| ru_position =Hooker, Scrumhalf\n| ru_amateuryears = \n| ru_amateurclubs =Col\u00e9gio S\u00e3o Luiz<br>Objetivo<br>Mau\u00e1<br>Nippon<br>Joerg Bruder<br>Bandeirantes\n| ru_clubyears = \n| ru_proclubs =\n| ru_clubcaps = \n| ru_clubpoints = \n| ru_nationalyears =1979-1995\n| ru_nationalteam = {{ru|Brazil}}\n| ru_nationalcaps =70\n| ru_nationalpoints =\n| ru_sevensnationalyears = \n| ru_sevensnationalteam  =\n| ru_sevensnationalcomp  = \n| ru_coachyears = \n| ru_coachclubs ={{ru|Brazil}}\n}}\n'''Ant\u00f4nio Martoni Neto''' (born [[S\u00e3o Paulo]], 1961) is a Brazilian former rugby union player, coach and he is currently a rugby commentator for [[ESPN]] Brazil. He played first as a hooker, later moving to scrum-half. He is professionally a lawyer. He is usually considered one of the best Brazilian rugby union players of ever.\n\nMartoni started his player career at Col\u00e9gio S\u00e3o Luiz. He later would play for Objetivo, Mau\u00e1, Nippon, Joerg Bruder and Bandeirantes, a team he helped to start, in 1983, and he would represent most of his career, finished in 2000. He also played football as a youngster and decided for rugby union over football at 18. He won for Bandeirantes the Brazilian Championship B Series title, in 1983, and 2 Brazilian Championship titles, in 1988 and 1995. He also won 4 S\u00e3o Paulo State Championship titles, in 1990, 1996, 1998 and 2000.\n\nMartoni had more than 70 caps for [[Brazil national rugby union team|Brazil]], from 1979 to 1995. He had his debut at the [[South American Rugby Championship]], at 7 October 1979, in a 53-6 loss to [[Chile national rugby union team|Chile]], in [[Vi\u00f1a del Mar]]. He scored his first points in that game.\n\nHe became a coach when he finished his player career, in 2000. He was the coach of Bandeirantes and at the same time of Brazil national team. He achieved Brazil first international titles, at the [[South American Rugby Championship]] B, in 2000 and 2002. He was also in charge of the Brazilian side during the [[2003 Rugby World Cup]] qualifyings, and after two years without losses, he managed to improve his [[International Rugby Board|IRB]] ranking position from 69th to 36th.<ref>[http://www.portaldorugby.com.br/noticia/39-entrevistas/1693-noticia-1793 Falando de Rugby: Ant\u00f4nio Martoni, Interview, 10 February 2011, Portal do Rugby (Portuguese)]{{dead link|date=October 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n\nMartoni is a rugby commentator for ESPN since 2003, he has been covering the most important international competitions for the sports channel.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.portaldorugby.com.br/noticia/39-entrevistas/1693-noticia-1793 Falando de Rugby: Ant\u00f4nio Martoni, Interview, 10 February 2011, Portal do Rugby (Portuguese)]{{dead link|date=October 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Martoni, Antonio}}\n[[Category:1961 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Brazilian rugby union players]]\n[[Category:Brazilian rugby union coaches]]\n[[Category:Rugby union hookers]]\n[[Category:Rugby union fly-halves]]\n\n{{Brazil-rugbyunion-bio-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Joeykai", "label": "safe", "comment": "clean up, addedorphantag", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ant%C3%B4nio_Martoni"}
{"title_page": "Tales from the Loop", "text_new": "{{short description|American drama TV series}}\n{{for|the series' source material|Tales from the Loop (role-playing game)}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name                = Tales from the Loop\n| image                    = \n| genre                    = [[Drama (film and television)|Drama]]<br>[[Science fiction|Science fiction]]\n| developer                = Nathaniel Halpern\n| based_on                 = {{based on|[[Tales from the Loop (role-playing game)|''Tales from the Loop'']]|[[Simon St\u00e5lenhag]]}}\n| starring                 = {{Plainlist|\n*[[Rebecca Hall]]\n*[[Jonathan Pryce]]\n}}\n| composer                 = {{Plainlist|\n*[[Philip Glass]]\n*[[Paul Leonard-Morgan]]\n}}\n| country                  = United States\n| language                 = English\n| num_seasons              = \n| num_episodes             = \n| list_episodes            = \n| executive_producer       = {{Plainlist|\n*[[Matt Reeves]]\n*Adam Kassan\n*Rafi Crohn\n*Nathaniel Halpern\n*[[Mark Romanek]]\n*Mattias Montero\n*Johan Lindstr\u00f6m\n*Samantha Taylor Pickett\n}}\n| producer                 = \n| cinematography           = \n| editor                   = \n| runtime                  = \n| company                  = {{Plainlist|\n*6th & Idaho\n*Indio\n*[[Amazon Studios]]\n*{{nowrap|[[Fox 21 Television Studios]]\n}}\n}}\n| network                  = [[Amazon Video]]\n| first_aired              = \n| last_aired               = \n| website                  = \n| image_alt                = \n| caption                  = \n| channel                  = \n| first_run                = \n| released                 = \n}}\n'''''Tales from the Loop''''' is an upcoming American [[science fiction television|science fiction]] [[Drama (film and television)|drama]] television series based on the eponymous art book by [[Simon St\u00e5lenhag]]. It is set to premiere on [[Amazon Video]]. On February 27, 2020, it was announced that the series will premiere on April 3, 2020.<ref>{{cite web|title=Video: \"Tales from the Loop\" - Official Trailer|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/video/2020/02/27/video-tales-from-the-loop-official-trailer-21214/20200227amazon01/|work=[[The Futon Critic]]|date=February 27, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Premise==\n'Inspired by the wondrous paintings of Simon St\u00e5lenhag, Tales from the Loop explores the mind-bending adventures of the people who live above the Loop, a machine built to unlock and explore the mysteries of the universe - making things previously relegated to science fiction, possible.\"<ref name=\"SeriesOrder\">{{cite web|last=Andreeva|first=Nellie|title='Tales From The Loop': Amazon Studios Orders Genre Series Based On Simon St\u00e5lenhag Art From Matt Reeves & Fox 21|url=https://deadline.com/2018/07/tales-from-the-loop-amazon-studios-orders-genre-series-based-simon-stalenhag-art-1202427982/|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=17 July 2018|accessdate=17 July 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Cast==\n*[[Rebecca Hall]] as Loretta<ref>{{cite web|author1=Nellie Andreeva|author2=Denise Petski|title='Tales From The Loop': Rebecca Hall To Star In Amazon Series Based On Simon St\u00e5lenhag Art|url=https://deadline.com/2019/03/tales-from-the-loop-rebecca-hall-star-amazon-genre-series-simon-stalenhag-art-1202567544/|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=1 March 2019|accessdate=3 March 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Tyler Barnhardt]] as Danny Jansson<ref>https://www.express.co.uk/showbiz/tv-radio/1188009/13-Reasons-Why-cast-series-Netflix-Who-plays-Charlie-St-George-Who-is-Tyler-Barnhardt</ref>\n\n==Episodes==\n{{Episode table |total_width= |background=#000000 |overall= |title= |director= |writer= |writerR=<ref name=\"WGA\">{{Cite web |url=https://directories.wga.org/project/1180106/tales-from-the-loop/ |title=Tales From The Loop |website=[[Writers Guild of America West]] |access-date=March 3, 2020}} Episodes with a credit date in 2019.</ref> |airdate= |airdateR=<ref name=\"TFC\">{{cite web |title=Tales from the Loop \u2013 Listings |url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/showatch/tales-from-the-loop/listings/ |website=[[The Futon Critic]] |accessdate=March 5, 2020}}</ref> |released=y |country=U.S. |episodes=\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 1\n |Title           = Pilot - Loop\n |DirectedBy      = [[Mark Romanek]]<ref name=\"HR1\"/>\n |WrittenBy       = Nathaniel Halpern\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|3}}\n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = 000\n}}\n<!--{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 2\n |Title           = \n |DirectedBy      = \n |WrittenBy       = \n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|3}}\n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = 000\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 3\n |Title           = \n |DirectedBy      = \n |WrittenBy       = \n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|3}}\n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = 000\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 4\n |Title           = \n |DirectedBy      = \n |WrittenBy       = \n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|3}}\n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = 000\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 5\n |Title           = \n |DirectedBy      = \n |WrittenBy       = \n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|3}}\n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = 000\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 6\n |Title           = \n |DirectedBy      = \n |WrittenBy       = \n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|3}}\n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = 000\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 7\n |Title           = \n |DirectedBy      = \n |WrittenBy       = \n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|3}}\n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = 000\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 8\n |Title           = \n |DirectedBy      = \n |WrittenBy       = \n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|3}}\n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = 000\n}}-->\n}}\n\nEpisodes of the first season include:{{efn|name=Order|Episodes are currently ordered as they appear on the [[Writers Guild of America West]] website.<ref name=\"WGA\"/>}}\n<!--Do NOT add to the episodes table until it has been confirmed by episode numbers with a reliable source or the episodes have been released!-->\n* \"Control\" written by Nathaniel Halpern\n* \"Echo Spere\" written by Nathaniel Halpern\n* \"Enemies\" written by Nathaniel Halpern\n* \"Home\" written by Nathaniel Halpern\n* \"Parallel\" written by Nathaniel Halpern\n* \"Stasis\" written by Nathaniel Halpern\n* \"Transpose\" written by Nathaniel Halpern\n{{notelist}}\n\n==Production==\nOn July 17, 2018, it was announced that [[Amazon (company)|Amazon]] had given the production, based on the narrative art book with the same title by [[Simon St\u00e5lenhag]], a series order for a first season consisting of eight episodes. Executive producers are set to include [[Matt Reeves]], Adam Kassan, Rafi Crohn, Nathaniel Halpern, [[Mark Romanek]], Mattias Montero, [[Johan Lindstr\u00f6m]], and Samantha Taylor Pickett. Halpern is also expected to serve as showrunner as Romanek is expected to direct the pilot episode. Production companies involved with the series are set to include 6th & Idaho, Indio, [[Amazon Studios]], and [[Fox 21 Television Studios]].<ref name=\"SeriesOrder\"/><ref name=\"HR1\">{{cite web|last=Goldberg|first=Lesley|title='Tales From the Loop' TV Series Set at Amazon|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/tales-loop-tv-series-set-at-amazon-1127706|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=July 17, 2018|accessdate=July 17, 2018|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Holloway|first=Daniel|title=Amazon Orders Sci-Fi Series 'Tales From the Loop'|url=https://variety.com/2018/tv/news/amazon-tales-from-the-loop-1202875431/|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=July 17, 2018|accessdate=July 17, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Amazon Video original series}}\n\n[[Category:2020s American drama television series]]\n[[Category:Amazon Video original programming]]\n[[Category:2020s American science fiction television series]]\n[[Category:English-language television programs]]\n[[Category:Television series by 20th Century Fox Television]]\n[[Category:Television series by Amazon Studios]]\n[[Category:Upcoming drama television series]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American drama TV series}}\n{{for|the series' source material|Tales from the Loop (role-playing game)}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name                = Tales from the Loop\n| image                    = \n| genre                    = [[Drama (film and television)|Drama]]<br>[[Science fiction|Science fiction]]\n| developer                = Nathaniel Halpern\n| based_on                 = {{based on|[[Tales from the Loop (role-playing game)|''Tales from the Loop'']]|[[Simon St\u00e5lenhag]]}}\n| starring                 = {{Plainlist|\n*[[Rebecca Hall]]\n*[[Jonathan Pryce]]\n}}\n| composer                 = {{Plainlist|\n*[[Philip Glass]]\n*[[Paul Leonard-Morgan]]\n}}\n| country                  = United States\n| language                 = English\n| num_seasons              = \n| num_episodes             = \n| list_episodes            = \n| executive_producer       = {{Plainlist|\n*[[Matt Reeves]]\n*Adam Kassan\n*Rafi Crohn\n*Nathaniel Halpern\n*[[Mark Romanek]]\n*Mattias Montero\n*Johan Lindstr\u00f6m\n*Samantha Taylor Pickett\n}}\n| producer                 = \n| cinematography           = \n| editor                   = \n| runtime                  = \n| company                  = {{Plainlist|\n*6th & Idaho\n*Indio\n*[[Amazon Studios]]\n*{{nowrap|[[Fox 21 Television Studios]]\n}}\n}}\n| network                  = [[Amazon Video]]\n| first_aired              = \n| last_aired               = \n| website                  = \n| image_alt                = \n| caption                  = \n| channel                  = \n| first_run                = \n| released                 = \n}}\n'''''Tales from the Loop''''' is an upcoming American [[science fiction television|science fiction]] [[Drama (film and television)|drama]] television series based on the eponymous art book by [[Simon St\u00e5lenhag]]. It is set to premiere on [[Amazon Video]]. On February 27, 2020, it was announced that the series will premiere on April 3, 2020.<ref>{{cite web|title=Video: \"Tales from the Loop\" - Official Trailer|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/video/2020/02/27/video-tales-from-the-loop-official-trailer-21214/20200227amazon01/|work=[[The Futon Critic]]|date=February 27, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Premise==\n''Tales from the Loop'' explores \"the town and people who live above 'The Loop,' a machine built to unlock and explore the mysteries of the universe \u2013 making things possible that were previously relegated only to science fiction.\"<ref name=\"SeriesOrder\">{{cite web|last=Andreeva|first=Nellie|title='Tales From The Loop': Amazon Studios Orders Genre Series Based On Simon St\u00e5lenhag Art From Matt Reeves & Fox 21|url=https://deadline.com/2018/07/tales-from-the-loop-amazon-studios-orders-genre-series-based-simon-stalenhag-art-1202427982/|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=17 July 2018|accessdate=17 July 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Cast==\n*[[Rebecca Hall]] as Loretta<ref>{{cite web|author1=Nellie Andreeva|author2=Denise Petski|title='Tales From The Loop': Rebecca Hall To Star In Amazon Series Based On Simon St\u00e5lenhag Art|url=https://deadline.com/2019/03/tales-from-the-loop-rebecca-hall-star-amazon-genre-series-simon-stalenhag-art-1202567544/|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=1 March 2019|accessdate=3 March 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Tyler Barnhardt]] as Danny Jansson<ref>https://www.express.co.uk/showbiz/tv-radio/1188009/13-Reasons-Why-cast-series-Netflix-Who-plays-Charlie-St-George-Who-is-Tyler-Barnhardt</ref>\n\n==Episodes==\n{{Episode table |total_width= |background=#000000 |overall= |title= |director= |writer= |writerR=<ref name=\"WGA\">{{Cite web |url=https://directories.wga.org/project/1180106/tales-from-the-loop/ |title=Tales From The Loop |website=[[Writers Guild of America West]] |access-da